  "type": "mcq",
  "stem": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">The width of a rectangular dance floor is <span class=\"italic\">w</span> feet. The length of the floor is 6 feet longer than its width. Which of the following expresses the perimeter, in feet, of the dance floor in terms of <span class=\"italic\">w</span> ?</p>\n",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 w plus 6\"></span></span></p>\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"4 w plus 12\"></span></span></p>\n"
